    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-02-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-02-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="1199"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1199">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/191.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Stadden</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Manzanillo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 26, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Complying with your telegraphic instructions February 24, I telegraphed Governor
                    of Colima as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>In compliance with instructions from Government, formal protest is hereby
                            made against imposition of war tax on American citizens.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>The Governor replied as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Replying to your telegram. This Government does not recognize the right
                            of foreigners to protest against laws of the country that as in this
                            case are not <pb facs="0851" n="735" xml:id="pg_735"/> contrary to
                            international rules, therefore please abstain from making unjustifiable
                            protest.</p>
                        <p rend="right">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Governor</hi>.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>The law requires payment of war tax by March tenth.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stadden</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
